OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780617775
OL,3,CRare Roman brooch found by metal
OL,4,Cdetectorist to go on show for first
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FAn "exquisite" Roman brooch discovered
OL,8,Fby a metal detectorist in Midlothian
OL,9,Fis to go on show for the first time in
OL,10,Fa major new exhibition.
OL,12,FDescribed as a "miniature
OL,13,Fmasterpiece", the rare bronze brooch
OL,14,Fblends local and Roman design styles
OL,15,Fin a unique way.
OL,17,FIt was discovered in a field near
OL,18,FPathhead by a metal detectorist in
OL,19,F2022 but it is thought that it was
OL,20,Fprobably made in northern England.
OL,26,@oD@DOUoD@NO]tD@POUuD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780617775
OL,3,CRare Roman brooch found by metal
OL,4,Cdetectorist to go on show for first
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FThe brooch will go on show for the
OL,8,Ffirst time in the exhibition Roman
OL,9,FScotland: Life on the Edge of Empire
OL,10,Fwhich opens at the National Museum of
OL,11,FScotland in Edinburgh in November.
OL,13,FDr Fraser Hunter, principal curator of
OL,14,Fprehistory and Roman archaeology at
OL,15,FNational Museums Scotland,said:"The
OL,16,FPathhead brooch is a miniature
OL,17,Fmasterpiece of craftworking and the
OL,18,Fdetails are exquisite.
OL,26,@wD@bOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780617775
OL,3,CRare Roman brooch found by metal
OL,4,Cdetectorist to go on show for first
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,F"Fancy Roman pieces like this were
OL,8,Funusual even at the time and were used
OL,9,Fto show off in local society.
OL,11,F"Whoever wore it would have been out
OL,12,Fto impress and I'm sure visitors will
OL,13,Fbe dazzled by it when they see it up
OL,14,Fclose in Roman Scotland: Life on the
OL,15,FEdge of Empire."
OL,17,FAt the time the brooch was made,
OL,18,Fcraftworkers took inspiration from
OL,19,Fbrooches brought in with the Roman
OL,20,Finvasion and added touches reflecting
OL,21,Flocal tastes and styles.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUwD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780617775
OL,3,CRare Roman brooch found by metal
OL,4,Cdetectorist to go on show for first
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FOther archaeological finds suggest
OL,8,Fthere was an Iron Age settlement in
OL,9,Fthe area around where the brooch was
OL,10,Ffound and that it was a community that
OL,11,Fengaged with Rome.
OL,13,FThe brooch features enamel which has
OL,14,Fbeen carefully laid out in a zig-zag
OL,15,Fpattern alternating between red and
OL,16,Fyellow blocks while the shape and
OL,17,Fdesign of the head of the brooch are
OL,18,Fsaid to be inspired by older
OL,19,Ftraditions of Celtic art.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780617775
OL,3,CRare Roman brooch found by metal
OL,4,Cdetectorist to go on show for first
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FScientific analysis suggests the
OL,8,Fsurface of the brooch was once coated
OL,9,Fwith tin, which would have created a
OL,10,Fsilvery sheen to set off the bright
OL,11,Fcolours.
OL,13,FExperts said such a rare and valuable
OL,14,Fbrooch is unlikely to have been
OL,15,Favailable to buy or trade.
OL,17,FIt is thought the brooch, which dates
OL,18,Fto around 100-160 AD, probably came
OL,19,Finto local hands as a gift from the
OL,20,FRoman world.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780617775
OL,3,CRare Roman brooch found by metal
OL,4,Cdetectorist to go on show for first
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FThe brooch may have been given to
OL,8,Finfluence a local leader and it is
OL,9,Fsuggested it was perhaps worn as a
OL,10,Fsymbol of status and favour in the new
OL,11,Fregime.
OL,13,FDr Hunter said: "We're really excited
OL,14,Fto be able to present new finds like
OL,15,Fthis, things that have never been seen
OL,16,Fbefore, because they're some of the
OL,17,Fthings that really help drive the
OL,18,Fstory and this, in particular, because
OL,19,Fit tells that story of interaction,
OL,20,Fbecause it's a style of brooch that
OL,21,Fmixes the local and the Roman."
OL,26,@uD@QOU}D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
